Dialogue: 0,2:00:59.92,2:01:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,- FBI  坐着别动  - FBI  坐着别动\N{\ren}- FBI. Stay seated. - FBI. Stay seated.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:10.00,2:01:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,- 请坐好  - 坐好\N{\ren}-Please remain seated! -Stay seated.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:11.76,2:01:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,你必须坐好  直到飞机停稳\N{\ren}You must stay seated until the aircraft has come to a complete stop.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:15.20,2:01:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,天啊\N{\ren}God almighty.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:06.54,2:02:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,你叫什么名字?\N{\ren}What's your name?
Dialogue: 0,2:02:55.21,2:02:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,把手放在脑后!\N{\ren}Hands behind your head!
Dialogue: 0,2:02:57.63,2:03:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,卡尔  请让我上车吧\N{\ren}Carl, get me in the car, please.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:01.09,2:03:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,让我上车吧\N{\ren}Get me in the car.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:04.00,2:03:04.91,Default,,0,0,0,,让他上车\N{\ren}Put him in.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:22.24,2:03:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,鉴于罪行的严重性...\N{\ren}Taking into account the gravity of these crimes
Dialogue: 0,2:03:25.56,2:03:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,放肆和逃避的行为...\N{\ren}your history of bold and elusive behavior
Dialogue: 0,2:03:29.26,2:03:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,及对美国法律的蔑视\N{\ren}and your complete lack of respect for the laws of the United States
Dialogue: 0,2:03:33.53,2:03:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,我不得不驳回你  将你作为少年犯对待的请求\N{\ren}I have no choice but to ignore your request to be treated as a minor
Dialogue: 0,2:03:38.78,2:03:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,判你在亚特兰大监视最严密的监狱服刑12年\N{\ren}and sentence you to 12 years in Atlanta's maximum security prison
Dialogue: 0,2:03:43.88,2:03:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,并强烈建议对你在整个服刑期间\N{\ren}and recommend strongly that you be kept in isolation
Dialogue: 0,2:03:47.50,2:03:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,进行隔离关押\N{\ren}for the entirety of that sentence.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:02.67,2:04:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,走那边的门\N{\ren}Use that door over there.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:10.21,2:04:12.19,Default,,0,0,0,,替我向大家问好\N{\ren}and give everyone my love.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:12.23,2:04:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,我一直都在想他们\N{\ren}I think about them all the time.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:32.60,2:04:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,圣诞快乐  弗兰克\N{\ren}Merry Christmas, Frank.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:36.79,2:04:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,我给你带来了几本漫画书\N{\ren}Hey, I got you some comic books here.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:46.27,2:04:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,你女儿怎样?\N{\ren}How's your daughter?
Dialogue: 0,2:04:47.63,2:04:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,- 她叫什么名字?  - 格雷斯\N{\ren}- What was her name? - Grace.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:50.80,2:04:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,我不知道\N{\ren}Well... I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:52.11,2:04:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,她跟母亲在芝加哥生活\N{\ren}she lives with her mother in Chicago
Dialogue: 0,2:04:53.51,2:04:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,我不常见她\N{\ren}and I don't get to see her much.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:57.05,2:04:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,箱子里是什么?\N{\ren}What's in the briefcase?
Dialogue: 0,2:04:59.97,2:05:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,我是在去机场的路上\N{\ren}Oh. I'm on my way to the airport.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:02.46,2:05:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,是个在明尼苏达州活动的伪造支票者\N{\ren}It's a paperhanger who's working his way through Minnesota.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:07.25,2:05:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,他  他搞得我们发疯\N{\ren}Aw, geez, he's... he's driving us crazy.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:09.75,2:05:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,你带支票来了吗?\N{\ren}You got any of the checks?
Dialogue: 0,2:05:11.03,2:05:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,对  我带了张他在...\N{\ren}Yeah, yeah, I got a... a counterfeit that he drew
Dialogue: 0,2:05:14.28,2:05:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,大湖储贷银行填写的假支票\N{\ren}on the Great Lakes savings and Loan.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:16.64,2:05:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,他使用一台模版机  和一台"木下"牌打字机\N{\ren}see, he's just using a stencil machine and an Underwood.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:19.86,2:05:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,- 伪造者是名银行出纳  - 什么?\N{\ren}- Yeah, it's a teller at the bank. - Say again?
Dialogue: 0,2:05:22.76,2:05:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,肯定是出纳  卡尔\N{\ren}I-It's definitely a teller, Carl.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:25.45,2:05:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,银行从来都是用手工封盖日期\N{\ren}I mean, banks, they always use hand-stamps for the dates, see.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:28.24,2:05:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,一遍遍使用  所以总有磨损\N{\ren}They get used over and over again so they always get worn out
Dialogue: 0,2:05:31.27,2:05:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,数字总是有断点\N{\ren}and the numbers are always cracking.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:32.88,2:05:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,6和9  你看  它们先磨损\N{\ren}The sixes and the nines... see, they go first.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:39.45,2:05:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢\N{\ren}Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:46.80,2:05:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,我想让你帮我看样东西\N{\ren}I'd like you to take a look at something for me.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:53.63,2:05:55.37,Default,,0,0,0,,告诉我你是怎么想的\N{\ren}Tell me what you think.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:59.26,2:06:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,这是假的\N{\ren}That's a fake.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:00.90,2:06:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,你还没看呢  怎么知道?\N{\ren}How do you know? You haven't looked at it.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:02.54,2:06:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,没有剪开的边\N{\ren}Well, there's no perforated edge, right?
Dialogue: 0,2:06:04.63,2:06:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,我是说  这张支票是手工裁的 不是从大张上剪下的\N{\ren}I mean, this... this check was hand-cut, not fed.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:08.85,2:06:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,没错\N{\ren}Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,2:06:10.20,2:06:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,纸是双层的\N{\ren}Paper is double-bonded
Dialogue: 0,2:06:11.76,2:06:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,作为银行支票太重了\N{\ren}much too heavy to be a bank check.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:15.08,2:06:17.99,Default,,0,0,0,,这磁墨  我能用手感觉到它的凸起\N{\ren}Magnetic ink, it's, uh, raised against my fingers
Dialogue: 0,2:06:17.99,2:06:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,应该是平的\N{\ren}instead of flat.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:20.74,2:06:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,并且闻起来不像支票专用墨\N{\ren}And this doesn't smell like MICR.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:22.06,2:06:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,是一种...  一种画图用墨\N{\ren}It's some kind of a... you know, some kind of a drafting ink.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:25.07,2:06:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,在文具店能买到这种墨\N{\ren}You know, the kind you get at a stationery store.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:33.05,2:06:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,弗兰克\N{\ren}Frank.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:35.46,2:06:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,有没有兴趣在联邦调查局经济犯罪科工作?\N{\ren}would you be interested in working with the FBI's Financial Crimes Unit?
Dialogue: 0,2:06:41.13,2:06:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,我在这里已经有工作了  送信\N{\ren}I already got a job here. You know, I, uh, deliver the mail.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:45.96,2:06:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,弗兰克  我们能把你从监狱里放出来\N{\ren}Frank, we have the power to take you out of prison.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:50.65,2:06:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,你将在联邦调查局的监护下\N{\ren}You'd be placed in the custody of the FBI
Dialogue: 0,2:06:52.34,2:06:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,服完剩下的刑期\N{\ren}where you'd serve out the remainder of your sentence
Dialogue: 0,2:06:54.54,2:06:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,作为联邦政府的雇员\N{\ren}as an employee of the federal government.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:58.98,2:07:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,在谁的监护下?\N{\ren}Under whose custody?
Dialogue: 0,2:07:09.94,2:07:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,我叫弗兰克·阿巴戈内尔\N{\ren}Hi. I-I'm Frank Abagnale.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:12.69,2:07:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,我应该今天开始工作\N{\ren}I'm supposed to start work here today.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:14.50,2:07:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,是个安排英国处女岛度假的旅游公司\N{\ren}It's a tour company operating out of the BVI.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:17.89,2:07:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,先生  阿巴戈内尔来了\N{\ren}sir, Mr. Abagnale is here.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:19.96,2:07:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,我会再打给你\N{\ren}I'm going to call you back.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:52.00,2:07:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,你好  卡尔\N{\ren}Hello, Carl.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:53.25,2:07:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,欢迎来到联邦调查局\N{\ren}Welcome to the FBI.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:54.90,2:07:56.97,Default,,0,0,0,,我带你看看工作的地方\N{\ren}I'll show you where you're working.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:04.77,2:08:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,卡尔  我要在这里工作多久?\N{\ren}Carl... how long do I have to work here?
Dialogue: 0,2:08:08.90,2:08:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,早上8点15分到晚上5点钟\N{\ren}It's 8:15 in the morning to 5:00 in the afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:12.08,2:08:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,午休45分钟\N{\ren}45 minutes for lunch.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:13.30,2:08:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,不是问这个\N{\ren}No, I...
Dialogue: 0,2:08:15.37,2:08:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,我是说  多久?\N{\ren}I mean, how long?
Dialogue: 0,2:08:18.98,2:08:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,每天\N{\ren}Every day.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:21.18,2:08:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,每天  直到我们放你走\N{\ren}Every day, Frank, till we let you go.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:16.75,2:09:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,- 什么事  - 卡尔\N{\ren}- Yeah. - Hey, Carl.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:21.28,2:09:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,- 进展如何  - 现在聊天不合适  弗兰克\N{\ren}- How you doing? - It's not a good time, Frank.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:23.92,2:09:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,我在为周末赶工\N{\ren}I'm clearing my desk for the weekend.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:29.47,2:09:32.43,Default,,0,0,0,,介意我明天来跟你一起工作吗?\N{\ren}Carl, you mind if I come to work with you tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,2:09:32.43,2:09:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,明天是星期六\N{\ren}Tomorrow is saturday.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:34.20,2:09:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,我要飞到芝加哥看我女儿\N{\ren}I'm flying to Chicago to see my daughter.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:36.19,2:09:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,星期一回来\N{\ren}I'll be back to work on Monday.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:37.60,2:09:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,去见格雷斯?\N{\ren}You're going to see Grace, huh?
Dialogue: 0,2:09:39.17,2:09:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,对  是我的计划\N{\ren}Well, that's the plan.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:44.40,2:09:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,星期一前我该干什么?\N{\ren}so what should I do till Monday?
Dialogue: 0,2:09:46.49,2:09:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,对不起  这我帮不了你  让一让\N{\ren}I'm sorry, kid, I can't help you there. Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:56.56,2:09:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,汉莱提\N{\ren}This is Handratty.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:58.54,2:10:00.33,Default,,0,0,0,,好  接过来\N{\ren}Oh, yeah, put him on.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:08.71,2:10:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,斯耶先生\N{\ren}Mr. Sawyer.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:10.59,2:10:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,你怎么样\N{\ren}How are you?
Dialogue: 0,2:10:12.34,2:10:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,我还有6张的支票\N{\ren}I have a half a dozen more checks
Dialogue: 0,2:10:13.98,2:10:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,关于那家英国处女岛旅游公司的\N{\ren}on that tour operator at the BVI.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:50.11,2:10:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,请乘坐美国航空 355航班...\N{\ren}American Airlines 355...
Dialogue: 0,2:10:52.95,2:10:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,飞往芝加哥和旧金山的...\N{\ren}serving Chicago and san Francisco...
Dialogue: 0,2:10:54.78,2:10:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,旅客准备登机\N{\ren}is now open for passenger check-in.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:57.14,2:10:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,你怎么办到的  弗兰克?\N{\ren}How'd you do it, Frank?
Dialogue: 0,2:11:00.47,2:11:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,你是怎么通过路易斯安娜州的律师考试的?\N{\ren}How'd you pass the bar in Louisiana?
Dialogue: 0,2:11:03.42,2:11:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,你来这干什么?\N{\ren}What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,2:11:06.11,2:11:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,听着\N{\ren}Listen...
Dialogue: 0,2:11:08.00,2:11:10.04,Default,,0,0,0,,我很抱歉给你惹了这么多麻烦\N{\ren}I'm sorry I put you through all this.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:10.04,2:11:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,你要是回到欧洲  会死在坡皮监狱的\N{\ren}You go back to Europe, you're gonna die in Perpignan Prison.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:12.88,2:11:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你想从美国逃跑\N{\ren}You try to run here in the states
Dialogue: 0,2:11:13.84,2:11:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,我们就会把你送回亚特兰大关50年\N{\ren}we'll send you back to Atlanta for 50 years.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:17.17,2:11:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道\N{\ren}I know that.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:20.45,2:11:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,我花了4年时间设法把你放出来\N{\ren}I spent four years trying to arrange your release.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:23.00,2:11:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,我得向我的老板\N{\ren}Had to convince my bosses at the FBI
Dialogue: 0,2:11:24.60,2:11:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,和首席检察官证明\N{\ren}and the Attorney General of the United states
Dialogue: 0,2:11:26.38,2:11:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,你不会逃跑\N{\ren}you wouldn't run.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:28.14,2:11:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,你为什么那样做呢?\N{\ren}Why'd you do it?
Dialogue: 0,2:11:30.94,2:11:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你是个孩子  - 我不是你的孩子\N{\ren}- You're just a kid. - I'm not your kid.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:34.04,2:11:36.05,Default,,0,0,0,,你说你要去芝加哥\N{\ren}You said you were going to Chicago.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:36.44,2:11:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,我女儿这个周末不能见我了\N{\ren}My daughter can't see me this weekend.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:38.27,2:11:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,她要去滑雪\N{\ren}she's going skiing.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:40.75,2:11:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,你说她4岁\N{\ren}You said she was four years old.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:42.40,2:11:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,你撒谎\N{\ren}You're lying.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:43.59,2:11:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,我离开时她4岁\N{\ren}she was four when I left.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:45.20,2:11:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,现在15岁了\N{\ren}Now she's 15.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:46.68,2:11:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,我太太再婚11年了\N{\ren}My wife's been remarried for 11 years.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:49.47,2:11:51.61,Default,,0,0,0,,我有时见格雷斯\N{\ren}I see Grace every now and again.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:52.26,2:11:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我不明白  - 你当然明白\N{\ren}- I don't understand. - Sure you do.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:55.90,2:11:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,有时说谎更容易\N{\ren}sometimes it's easier living the lie.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:01.95,2:12:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,我今晚让你飞走  弗兰克\N{\ren}I'm going to let you fly tonight, Frank.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:04.90,2:12:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,我甚至不会拦你的\N{\ren}I'm not even going to try to stop you.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:06.72,2:12:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,因为我知道  你星期一会回来\N{\ren}That's 'cause I know you'll be back on Monday.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:09.63,2:12:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,是吗  你怎么知道我会回来?\N{\ren}Yeah? How do you know I'll come back?
Dialogue: 0,2:12:15.85,2:12:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,看\N{\ren}Look.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:17.90,2:12:18.99,Default,,0,0,0,,弗兰克\N{\ren}Frank.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:19.40,2:12:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,没有人在追你\N{\ren}nobody's chasing you.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:23.15,2:12:25.41,Default,,0,0,0,,前往匹兹堡的\N{\ren}American Airlines flight 131
Dialogue: 0,2:12:25.41,2:12:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,美航131航班  已开始登机\N{\ren}to Pittsburgh is now ready for boarding.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:27.53,2:12:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,持登机牌的乘客  请到23A门\N{\ren}Passengers with boarding passes, please proceed to Gate 23A.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:40.34,2:12:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,好的\N{\ren}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:41.90,2:12:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,爱丽丝  他还没来电吗?\N{\ren}Alice, has he still not called?
Dialogue: 0,2:12:44.39,2:12:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,是的  还没有\N{\ren}No, he hasn't.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:57.90,2:12:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,早上好\N{\ren}Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:59.08,2:13:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,我召开此次会议是为了讨论\N{\ren}I've, uh, called this meeting to discuss
Dialogue: 0,2:13:01.44,2:13:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,一种新型的支票欺诈和伪造手段\N{\ren}a new type of check fraud and counterfeiting
Dialogue: 0,2:13:03.81,2:13:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,嫌疑犯涂改支票\N{\ren}which the unsub is washing and altering checks
Dialogue: 0,2:13:05.83,2:13:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,然后发送到亚利桑那州\N{\ren}then passing them throughout Arizona.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:11.89,2:13:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,这个嫌疑犯是个大赌徒\N{\ren}This unsub is a big dog
Dialogue: 0,2:13:14.20,2:13:16.29,Default,,0,0,0,,支票填5位数\N{\ren}passing checks as large as five figures.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:19.35,2:13:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,对不起  我迟到了\N{\ren}sorry I'm late.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:22.40,2:13:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,抱歉\N{\ren}sorry.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:27.92,2:13:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,瑞特特工的桌子上有张伪造的支票\N{\ren}We have a recovered check on Agent Reiter's desk.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:30.74,2:13:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,我们出去看看吧\N{\ren}Why don't we step out to the bullpen?
Dialogue: 0,2:13:37.71,2:13:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,每一行都被加重\N{\ren}There's impressions on every line.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:41.88,2:13:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,好像原来数额是60美元\N{\ren}Looks like the original amount was for $60.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:49.00,2:13:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,我能看一下吗?\N{\ren}Mind if I take a look?
Dialogue: 0,2:13:53.80,2:13:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,一周前在福莱格斯达福兑现的\N{\ren}Cashed in Flagstaff a week ago.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:58.83,2:14:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,银行损失1万6千美元\N{\ren}Cost the bank $16,000.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:02.62,2:14:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,- 是张真支票  - 对\N{\ren}- It's a real check. - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:05.40,2:14:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,被洗过了\N{\ren}Yeah. It's been washed.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:06.76,2:14:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,原来的东西只剩下签名\N{\ren}The only thing original is the signature.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:09.00,2:14:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,但是很完美  卡尔  真的\N{\ren}But it's perfect, Carl. I mean...
Dialogue: 0,2:14:10.73,2:14:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,它不是用酸洗或漂白的\N{\ren}I mean this isn't hydrochloride or bleach.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:14.30,2:14:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,不是\N{\ren}No.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:15.47,2:14:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,是什么新东西\N{\ren}something new.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:17.25,2:14:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,也许是一种指甲膏清洗剂或者丙酮\N{\ren}Maybe a nail polish remover where the acetone
Dialogue: 0,2:14:19.41,2:14:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,之类的东西洗去手写墨水\N{\ren}removes the ink that's not been printed?
Dialogue: 0,2:14:25.20,2:14:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,你是怎么做的?  弗兰克?\N{\ren}How did you do it, Frank?
Dialogue: 0,2:14:28.30,2:14:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,你是怎么骗过路易斯安娜州的律师考试的?\N{\ren}How did you cheat on the bar exam in Louisiana?
Dialogue: 0,2:14:36.80,2:14:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,我没作弊\N{\ren}I didn't cheat.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:40.00,2:14:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,我学了两周就通过了\N{\ren}I studied for two weeks and I passed.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:44.82,2:14:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,是真的吗?  弗兰克?\N{\ren}Is that the truth, Frank?
Dialogue: 0,2:14:47.60,2:14:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,是真的吗?\N{\ren}Is that the truth?
Dialogue: 0,2:14:48.51,2:14:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,我肯定这家伙从邮箱里偷支票\N{\ren}I'll bet this guy steals checks out of mailboxes.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:51.94,2:14:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,他洗掉他们的名字  换成自己的\N{\ren}He washes off their names and he puts on his own.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:56.30,2:14:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,你说他是当地人?\N{\ren}You're saying that he's a local?
Dialogue: 0,2:14:58.83,2:15:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,如果是我的话\N{\ren}Well, if it were me, you know
Dialogue: 0,2:15:00.14,2:15:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,我会先给银行打电话  查一下余额...\N{\ren}I'd call the bank first, I'd check out the balance...
Dialogue: 0,2:15:02.51,2:15:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,弄清楚有足够的钱在里面\N{\ren}Make sure there's enough money in there
Dialogue: 0,2:15:04.20,2:15:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,- 确定值得冒险  - 正是如此\N{\ren}- to make it worth your while. - Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:06.50,2:15:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,卡尔  我想这家伙非常狡猾\N{\ren}You know, Carl, I think this guy's pretty smart.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:09.80,2:15:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,我想现在我们要做的就是去抓住他\N{\ren}I guess all we have to do now is catch him.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:14.04,2:15:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,那就是今早的第一件事\N{\ren}We'll start first thing in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:16.14,2:15:19.31,Default,,0,0,0,,我们开始追查这个名叫埃里克·安东尼家伙\N{\ren}We'll run the name Eric Anthony Feeders.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:19.31,2:15:21.37,Default,,0,0,0,,在内华大  亚利桑那  加利福尼亚各州\N{\ren}In Nevada, Arizona, California.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:21.42,2:15:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,所有的名字  是吗?  克里斯·弗兰克也要注意?\N{\ren}Both names, right? Chris Frank, too?
Dialogue: 0,2:15:23.32,2:15:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,没错...\N{\ren}Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,2:15:13.96,2:15:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\a6\fs22\fad(300,300)}小弗兰克·阿巴戈内尔已经结婚26年
Dialogue: 0,2:15:17.96,2:15:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\a6\fs22\fad(300,300)}有三个儿子  在中西部过着平静的生活
Dialogue: 0,2:15:21.96,2:15:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\a6\fs22\fad(300,300)}自从1974年出狱后
Dialogue: 0,2:15:25.96,2:15:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\a6\fs22\fad(300,300)}弗兰克帮助FBI抓住了一些世界上隐藏最深的支票造假者
Dialogue: 0,2:15:29.96,2:15:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\a6\fs22\fad(300,300)}被认为是世界上最著名的反银行诈骗和欺诈专家
Dialogue: 0,2:15:34.56,2:15:42.80,Default,,0,0,70,,{\fs22\fad(300,300)}弗兰克还设计了银行和\N世界500强公司每天都在使用的安全支票
Dialogue: 0,2:15:43.20,2:15:47.85,Default,,0,0,80,,{\fs22\fad(300,300)}这些公司每年向小弗兰克·阿巴戈内尔\N支付几百万美元的服务费用
Dialogue: 0,2:15:48.85,2:15:54.10,Default,,0,0,80,,{\fs22\fad(300,300)}弗兰克和卡尔至今仍然是好友
